content:
# Chemistry Components

Create educational chemistry visualizations including periodic tables, element displays, and chemical formulas with proper formatting.

## Example 1: Complete Periodic Table

Display the complete periodic table with element highlighting and category coloring.

```javascript
import {
  Artboard,
  Card,
  Container,
  Text,
  TextArea,
  PeriodicTable,
} from "w2l";

const artboard = new Artboard({
  width: 1200,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 40 },
});

const card = new Card({
  width: 1120,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 20 },
});

const title = new Text({
  content: "Complete Periodic Table of Elements",
  fontSize: 18,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});

const description = new TextArea({
  content: "The periodic table organizes all 118 chemical elements by their atomic structure. Elements in the same group (column) have similar chemical properties.",
  width: 1080,
  fontSize: 12,
  lineHeight: 1.5,
});

// Create periodic table with highlighted elements (H, C, N, O - essential for life)
const periodicTable = new PeriodicTable({
  cellWidth: 55,
  cellHeight: 65,
  spacing: 3,
  highlightElements: [1, 6, 7, 8],
  selectElements: [11], // Na - selected
  showMass: true,
  includeLanthanides: true, // Show all 118 elements
});

const content = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "vertical",
  spacing: 15,
});

content.add(title);
content.add(description);
content.add(periodicTable.container);
card.add(content);
artboard.add(card);

return artboard.render();
```

## Example 2: Individual Element Display

Display individual elements from different categories with custom styling.

```javascript
import {
  Artboard,
  Card,
  Container,
  Text,
  PeriodicElement,
  ElementCategory,
} from "w2l";

const artboard = new Artboard({
  width: 1200,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 40 },
});

const card = new Card({
  width: 1120,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 20 },
});

const title = new Text({
  content: "Element Categories & Examples",
  fontSize: 18,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});

// Create container for sample elements
const elementsContainer = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "horizontal",
  spacing: 15,
  horizontalAlignment: "center",
});

// Hydrogen - highlighted nonmetal
const hydrogen = new PeriodicElement({
  element: {
    number: 1,
    symbol: "H",
    name: "Hydrogen",
    mass: 1.008,
    category: ElementCategory.NONMETAL,
  },
  width: 80,
  height: 90,
  highlighted: true,
});

// Carbon - highlighted nonmetal
const carbon = new PeriodicElement({
  element: {
    number: 6,
    symbol: "C",
    name: "Carbon",
    mass: 12.011,
    category: ElementCategory.NONMETAL,
  },
  width: 80,
  height: 90,
  highlighted: true,
});

// Sodium - selected alkali metal
const sodium = new PeriodicElement({
  element: {
    number: 11,
    symbol: "Na",
    name: "Sodium",
    mass: 22.990,
    category: ElementCategory.ALKALI_METAL,
  },
  width: 80,
  height: 90,
  selected: true,
});

// Gold - transition metal
const gold = new PeriodicElement({
  element: {
    number: 79,
    symbol: "Au",
    name: "Gold",
    mass: 196.967,
    category: ElementCategory.TRANSITION_METAL,
  },
  width: 80,
  height: 90,
});

// Helium - noble gas
const helium = new PeriodicElement({
  element: {
    number: 2,
    symbol: "He",
    name: "Helium",
    mass: 4.003,
    category: ElementCategory.NOBLE_GAS,
  },
  width: 80,
  height: 90,
});

elementsContainer.add(hydrogen.element);
elementsContainer.add(carbon.element);
elementsContainer.add(sodium.element);
elementsContainer.add(gold.element);
elementsContainer.add(helium.element);

const content = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "vertical",
  spacing: 15,
});

content.add(title);
content.add(elementsContainer);
card.add(content);
artboard.add(card);

return artboard.render();
```

## Example 3: Chemical Formulas and Reactions

Display chemical formulas with proper subscript formatting and reaction equations.

```javascript
import {
  Artboard,
  Card,
  Container,
  Text,
  ChemicalFormula,
} from "w2l";

const artboard = new Artboard({
  width: 1200,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 40 },
});

const card = new Card({
  width: 1120,
  height: "auto",
  boxModel: { padding: 20 },
});

const title = new Text({
  content: "Chemical Formulas & Reactions",
  fontSize: 18,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});

const formulasContainer = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "vertical",
  spacing: 20,
});

// Water formula - simple compound
const waterLabel = new Text({
  content: "Water (Hâ‚‚O):",
  fontSize: 14,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});
const waterFormula = new ChemicalFormula("H2O", 16);
const waterRow = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "horizontal",
  spacing: 15,
  verticalAlignment: "center",
});
waterRow.add(waterLabel);
waterRow.add(waterFormula.element);

// Combustion of methane - reaction with arrow
const combustionLabel = new Text({
  content: "Combustion of Methane:",
  fontSize: 14,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});
const combustionFormula = new ChemicalFormula("CH4 + 2O2 -> CO2 + 2H2O", 14);
const combustionRow = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "horizontal",
  spacing: 15,
  verticalAlignment: "center",
});
combustionRow.add(combustionLabel);
combustionRow.add(combustionFormula.element);

// Photosynthesis - complex biological reaction
const photoLabel = new Text({
  content: "Photosynthesis:",
  fontSize: 14,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});
const photoFormula = new ChemicalFormula("6CO2 + 6H2O -> C6H12O6 + 6O2", 14);
const photoRow = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "horizontal",
  spacing: 15,
  verticalAlignment: "center",
});
photoRow.add(photoLabel);
photoRow.add(photoFormula.element);

// Common compounds - multiple formulas in a row
const compoundsLabel = new Text({
  content: "Common Compounds:",
  fontSize: 14,
  style: { fontWeight: "bold" },
});
const saltFormula = new ChemicalFormula("NaCl", 14); // Table salt
const sugarFormula = new ChemicalFormula("C12H22O11", 14); // Sucrose
const ammoniaFormula = new ChemicalFormula("NH3", 14); // Ammonia
const compoundsRow = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "horizontal",
  spacing: 20,
  verticalAlignment: "center",
});
compoundsRow.add(compoundsLabel);
compoundsRow.add(saltFormula.element);
compoundsRow.add(sugarFormula.element);
compoundsRow.add(ammoniaFormula.element);

formulasContainer.add(waterRow);
formulasContainer.add(combustionRow);
formulasContainer.add(photoRow);
formulasContainer.add(compoundsRow);

const content = new Container({
  width: 1080,
  height: "auto",
  direction: "vertical",
  spacing: 15,
});

content.add(title);
content.add(formulasContainer);
card.add(content);
artboard.add(card);

return artboard.render();
```

## Key Features

- **PeriodicTable**: Display the complete periodic table with 118 elements, category coloring, highlighting, and selection
- **PeriodicElement**: Show individual elements with atomic number, symbol, name, mass, and category-based styling
- **ChemicalFormula**: Render chemical formulas with proper subscript formatting and support for reaction arrows (->)
- **ElementCategory**: Categorize elements (ALKALI_METAL, NOBLE_GAS, NONMETAL, TRANSITION_METAL, etc.)
